{"id":"0193e16c-6d02-40b9-9bb3-95e80f500e38","type":"main-list-block","metadata":{"filename":"1510-01-[0193e16c].json","folder":"michelangelo-letters","focus":{"blockId":"aa1f9edc-1e21-48df-b12f-29616403f71f","caret":666}},"blockProperties":[],"children":[{"id":"f81cbb50-3b8f-4a42-a51e-ab7d1fb92689","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, [January, 1510].\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"d1b9d5f2-93e6-4093-8fc3-3e934994fb31","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","text":"Rom","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"e2305acc-2398-4373-936c-4b9093062809","type":"codex/time-reference","start":12,"end":24,"value":"0edb2d4e-c2a6-4f6b-a67a-666c5175d365","text":"January, 151","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"34d9785e-5f41-45e9-9ce6-38e7433709bd","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"25c0da12-7f9e-4021-88c5-f59b7a1e7613","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lodovico di Buonarrota Simoni,\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"0bb9dd08-8849-4619-a44c-d4bbd371df5b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"21671569-3eea-412b-85cc-08f659f58019","text":"Lodovico di Buonarrota Simon","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"cd49239a-eac5-4695-ba61-e2bde5f185e5","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"0d6985a7-9978-4698-9212-57093376a5eb","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"293969e8-beac-43a9-93bc-17a98d057440","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","text":"Florenc","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"408a4962-4f29-451b-918f-59a7473e643c","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"15c8e44c-3c55-4532-99a6-f4e7387c0517","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"aa1f9edc-1e21-48df-b12f-29616403f71f","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Dearest Father, — I am sending you a hundred broad ducats in gold which you are to give to Buonarroto and the others, and for which you are to make me their creditor with the shop as security. If they do their utmost to succeed, I will help them from time to time to the best of my ability — tell them so. Go, therefore, on receipt of this, to Bonifazio [Fazi] or to Lorenzo Benintendi, both you and Buonarroto, and he will pay over the money. He will pay you a hundred broad ducats in gold, in exchange for an equal sum given by me here to Baldassare Balducci. I wrote in reply to your remark about buying to say that this is not the proper time. As for my affairs here, I will do the best I can, God helping me. I wrote to you about that boy, saying his father was to send for him and that I would give him no more money. This I now confirm: the carrier has already received quite enough to cover his return journey. The boy is all right for Florence, where he can stay at home and study and be with his father and mother but here he is not worth so much as a quattrino, and he keeps me slaving like a beast, while my other boy is not yet well enough to get up. In fact I have not kept him in the house here, for when I was so distracted and could bear with him no longer I sent him off to share the room of a brother of his. I have no money. I have had to wring my very heart strings to send what I am sending you now, and I do not feel justified in asking for any more, for I have no assistants working under me, and I alone am doing but little. When I have arranged about this house business I hope to begin work in earnest. \r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"7e022860-db45-4b34-8444-21961d85747c","type":"codex/en